Rating: 3
A very good, and tasty dish. My changes included adding one tablespoon of Parmesan and Romano chesse (a little more bite), and using single rib chops and coating both sides with the pesto. The latter change forced me to reduce the heat to 400 degrees, and cooks for 8 minutes per side for medium rare.

Rating: 4
I made this using prepared(Costco) pesto to which I added extra fresh, finely chopped rosemary,basil and parsley. I skillet browned the meat before putting on the pesto, then baked it at 325F until the remote reading thermometer read 122F. After tenting with foil for 10min the temp was 137 and perfectly rare to med rare.

Rating: 4
Fantastic! I made this exactly as directed with one small exception: I used 3 1 pound racks (served 4 easily) with same amount of pesto, cooking time likely varies by size of rack. The lamb was exceptionally delicious, moist and tender. I had not prepared rack of lamb before and search the website for ideas; this one does not require any pre-browning and is very straightforward to prepare. I look forward to making it again.

